  "prompt": "Where can I find affordable cake shops on the Gold Coast?",
  "response": "Finding affordable cake shops on the Gold Coast can be done with a little research. Here are some places to start your search, combining different types of businesses that offer cakes:\n\n**1. Supermarkets:**\n\n*   **Coles & Woolworths:** These major supermarkets often have in-house bakeries that produce cakes at reasonable prices. They're great for basic birthday cakes or sheet cakes for parties. Check their websites or visit your local store.\n\n**2. Cake Shops & Bakeries (Price-Focused):**\n\n*   **Look for smaller, independent bakeries:** Often, they can offer more competitive pricing compared to larger chains. Look for shops located outside of high-rent tourist areas, as rent often impacts price. Google Maps search using terms like \"cake shop\" or \"bakery\" and then filter by review count or visit shops in person to compare prices.\n*   **Outlet Bakeries:** Occasionally, you might find outlet stores for larger bakeries, which sell slightly imperfect cakes or day-old goods at discounted prices.  These can be a great option if presentation isn't your top priority. (This is a more general suggestion, search specifically for outlet bakeries in the Gold Coast)\n\n**3. Home-Based Bakers:**\n\n*   **Facebook Marketplace & Community Groups:** Search for local \"baker\" or \"cake\" groups on Facebook, and also browse the Marketplace. Home-based bakers often have lower overhead costs and can offer custom cakes for more affordable prices than established shops.  Always check reviews and ask for references.\n*   **Instagram:** Search for local Gold Coast bakers using hashtags like #goldcoastcakes #goldcoastbaker #goldcoastbirthdaycakes.  Look for profiles that showcase their work and offer reasonable pricing.\n\n**4. Consider Alternatives:**\n\n*   **DIY Cake Kits:** If you're feeling creative, you can purchase a cake mix and decorating supplies. This is often the cheapest option, although it requires some effort.\n*   **Cake Toppers & Decorations:** If you already have a simple cake, you can dress it up with affordable cake toppers and decorations from stores like Kmart, Spotlight, or discount party supply shops. This can make a store-bought cake look more special without breaking the bank.\n\n**Tips for Finding Affordable Cakes:**\n\n*   **Be specific about your budget:** When contacting bakers, clearly state your maximum budget. This helps them suggest options that fit within your price range.\n*   **Keep the design simple:** Intricate designs and elaborate decorations drive up the cost. Choose a simpler design or opt for fewer decorations.\n*   **Order in advance:** Last-minute orders often incur rush fees.\n*   **Consider a smaller cake:** If you don't need a large cake, opt for a smaller size.\n*   **Check for promotions or discounts:** Some bakeries offer discounts for first-time customers or during certain times of the year.\n*   **Compare prices:** Get quotes from several different bakeries before making a decision.\n*   **Read reviews:** Check online reviews to get an idea of the quality and service of different bakeries.\n*   **Ask about ingredients:** If you have any dietary restrictions or allergies, be sure to ask about the ingredients used in the cake.\n\nBy using these resources and tips, you should be able to find an affordable and delicious cake on the Gold Coast for your next celebration! Good luck!\n",
